
1. What is Design Pattern?
Answer: According to Christopher Alexander - Each pattern describes a problem which occurs over and over again in our environment, and then describes 
        the core of the solution to that problem, in such a way that you can use this solution a miilion times over, without ever doing it the same way twice.

2. Essential Elements of a pattern:
    a. Pattern Name
    b. Problem.
    c. Solution.
    d. Consequences.
